ly by\na transfer of energy from the ions to electrons via Coulomb collisions, which\nis reasonable for the accretion with a lower mass accretion rate. Coulomb\nheating is the dominated heating mechanism for the electrons only if the\nmagnetic field is strongly sub-equipartition, which is roughly consistent with\nobservations.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sat, 31 Aug 2013 10:13:47 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-17"}
